WEBVTT

00:01.566 --> 00:04.656
♪

00:33.163 --> 00:35.339
[men shouting]

00:35.383 --> 00:38.038
[raucous shouting]

00:46.176 --> 00:50.050
[rhythmic grunting and clapping]

00:56.230 --> 00:59.146
[shouting continues]

01:11.723 --> 01:12.898
[splashing]

01:14.422 --> 01:15.553
LINCOLN:
You gotta do something;
my brother is innocent.

01:15.597 --> 01:16.815
He's an American
citizen.

01:16.859 --> 01:18.469
Look, there's nothing
I can do about that.

01:18.513 --> 01:20.123
Of course there is--
back at the crime scene,
that'll prove...

01:20.167 --> 01:21.211
Look, I'm a night
clerk, okay?

01:21.255 --> 01:22.473
If you want someone
who can really

01:22.517 --> 01:23.735
do something, you're
gonna have to wait

01:23.779 --> 01:26.260
for the consul;
he gets in in the morning.

01:26.303 --> 01:27.913
I'm sorry.

01:29.045 --> 01:30.742
That ain't gonna cut it.

01:32.135 --> 01:33.180
Your brother,

01:33.223 --> 01:35.269
where do they have
him incarcerated?

01:35.312 --> 01:36.226
Sona.

01:36.270 --> 01:37.575
[sighs]

01:37.619 --> 01:39.186
What?

01:41.144 --> 01:43.320
The worst of the worst
are there,

01:43.364 --> 01:46.106
men no other prison will take.

01:51.807 --> 01:54.288
They rioted so badly
a year ago,

01:54.331 --> 01:56.116
the guards pulled out,

01:56.159 --> 01:57.856
just left them
to themselves.

01:57.900 --> 02:02.209
A thousand thieves,
rapists, murderers.

02:14.264 --> 02:15.700
keeps the perimeter.

02:19.226 --> 02:20.270
[bone cracks]

02:25.580 --> 02:29.279
To them, Sona's
a one-way street.

02:29.323 --> 02:31.281
What goes in...

02:31.325 --> 02:33.240
never comes out...

02:33.283 --> 02:35.372
unless it's dead.

03:26.510 --> 03:29.426
MAN:
Somebody didn't do their
due diligence on this guy,

03:29.470 --> 03:31.863
and we need him moved
to a facility that's a little

03:31.907 --> 03:33.082
more... moderate.

03:33.125 --> 03:34.475
All right?

03:34.518 --> 03:35.998
Thank you.

03:36.041 --> 03:37.478
All right, the good news
is as of yesterday

03:37.521 --> 03:38.783
you're a free man.

03:38.827 --> 03:40.263
You got nothing
to worry about.

03:40.307 --> 03:41.656
Just my brother.

03:41.699 --> 03:43.962
Right. Well, that's a heck
of a story, you two.

03:44.006 --> 03:46.051
That made the news
even down here.

03:46.095 --> 03:48.358
And I understand you have
a son as well?

03:48.402 --> 03:50.012
Yeah. Uh-huh.LJ-- Lincoln Jr.?

03:50.055 --> 03:51.448
He must be ecstatic about your
exoneration.

03:51.492 --> 03:53.624
Still trying to reach him.

03:53.668 --> 03:55.452
Well, hey, tell us where he is.

03:55.496 --> 03:57.149
We'll send...Let me handle that.

03:57.193 --> 03:58.803
Let's just focus
on Michael.

03:58.847 --> 04:01.371
Okay, well, good news is
is that much

04:01.415 --> 04:03.852
of what you're saying is
checking out at the crime scene.

04:03.895 --> 04:06.463
The victim did have
a service revolver

04:06.507 --> 04:08.422
with U.S. government numbers
on it.

04:08.465 --> 04:10.815
And if a weapon was found,
then that lends

04:10.859 --> 04:12.426
real credence
to self-defense

04:12.469 --> 04:14.210
as a motive.
Great.

04:14.254 --> 04:16.560
They, uh, find anything else?

04:16.604 --> 04:18.823
Like what?
A bag.

04:18.867 --> 04:19.998
What was in it?

04:20.042 --> 04:21.783
A little money.

04:21.826 --> 04:22.697
Sorry.

04:22.740 --> 04:23.828
Of course
they didn't.

04:23.872 --> 04:25.482
Yeah, well, whatever the case,

04:25.526 --> 04:27.136
regarding Michael,
I have managed

04:27.179 --> 04:28.442
to make a little headway.

04:28.485 --> 04:29.747
I arranged
for a transfer

04:29.791 --> 04:31.140
for your brother
to another facility,

04:31.183 --> 04:32.315
effective tomorrow.

04:32.359 --> 04:33.534
It's a lot safer,

04:33.577 --> 04:35.057
it's a lot cleaner.Great.

04:35.100 --> 04:38.843
And if this is stacking up
like I think it is,

04:38.887 --> 04:41.368
I'd be pretty confident
the charges will be dropped.

04:41.411 --> 04:43.065
He'd be free?

04:43.108 --> 04:45.415
Well, he'd still face charges
in the U.S.

04:45.459 --> 04:47.243
But out of there?

04:47.287 --> 04:49.071
Yes.

04:57.384 --> 04:58.907
[flies buzzing]

05:17.099 --> 05:19.928
[harsh scraping]

05:38.163 --> 05:40.427
BELLICK:
Is there...
is there a mess hall here?

05:40.470 --> 05:42.385
Mess hall?

05:42.429 --> 05:44.300
And some water.

05:44.344 --> 05:46.607
I'm dying of thirst. Please.

05:46.650 --> 05:48.652
Please.

05:48.696 --> 05:50.262
There's some water.

05:55.224 --> 05:56.312
Bite me.

05:58.445 --> 05:59.446
What'd you say?

05:59.489 --> 06:00.577
I didn't say nothing.

06:03.580 --> 06:05.930
Drink it.

06:05.974 --> 06:06.888
You hear me?

06:06.931 --> 06:09.194
Drink!

06:17.594 --> 06:21.337
[all laughing]

06:26.255 --> 06:29.476
Hey, get used to it, man.

06:29.519 --> 06:32.435
I haven't eaten for days.

06:32.479 --> 06:34.611
Come on.

06:39.529 --> 06:42.402
[overlapping chatter]

06:51.889 --> 06:53.543
[camera shutters snapping]

07:19.656 --> 07:21.789
♪

07:21.832 --> 07:26.010
[man cackling nearby]

07:36.194 --> 07:37.718
How are you doing?

07:37.761 --> 07:39.197
What do you want, Alex?

07:39.241 --> 07:42.679
You're so clever-- like
planting the drugs on the boat.

07:42.723 --> 07:43.637
That's a big irony.

07:43.680 --> 07:45.856
Lawman in jail.

07:45.900 --> 07:47.684
You are exactly where
you belong.

07:47.728 --> 07:48.946
No, that's where
you're wrong.

07:48.990 --> 07:50.252
And that's where
you're gonna help me.

07:50.295 --> 07:51.862
I will have a court date
one of these days,

07:51.906 --> 07:53.298
and you will be there
on the stand.

07:53.342 --> 07:55.649
And you will tell the truth
that you planted this

07:55.692 --> 07:58.129
and you set this up,
and I'm gonna go home.

07:58.173 --> 08:02.264
That's funny, I could have
sworn you set this up.

08:03.874 --> 08:06.616
I set this up?
I'm in here.

08:06.660 --> 08:08.052
What does the Company
want with me?

08:08.096 --> 08:09.271
Why Panama?

08:09.314 --> 08:11.665
What, you think I know
what they wanted?

08:11.708 --> 08:14.145
They had me.

08:14.189 --> 08:15.451
I did what they

08:15.495 --> 08:17.584
asked me to do-- arrest you

08:17.627 --> 08:18.802
in Panama and
hand you over.

08:18.846 --> 08:20.717
That's it. That's, that's...

08:23.894 --> 08:26.157
That's old news, huh?

08:26.201 --> 08:28.682
This is the first day
of the rest of our lives.

08:28.725 --> 08:30.684
How about we work
together, you know?

08:30.727 --> 08:32.599
Help each other out.

08:32.642 --> 08:34.470
Except every time I look at you,

08:34.514 --> 08:37.299
all I can see is the man
who killed my father.

08:39.214 --> 08:40.607
You're on your own.

08:49.616 --> 08:52.444
WOMAN [yelling]:

08:59.974 --> 09:02.542
[yelling continues]

09:03.891 --> 09:06.154
[yelling continues]

09:07.242 --> 09:09.157
[buzzer sounds]

09:13.074 --> 09:14.989
Sign here to say
that once inside,

09:15.032 --> 09:16.730
you're on your own
by the law,

09:16.773 --> 09:17.687
that you're not protected
by the military

09:17.731 --> 09:19.167
in case of an assault.

09:19.210 --> 09:21.778
And any attempt
to assist an inmate
trying to escape

09:21.822 --> 09:23.258
will be met
with a lethal response.

09:23.301 --> 09:25.173
Wouldn't dream of it.

09:29.481 --> 09:32.136
[door opens and shuts]

09:40.754 --> 09:42.930
So...

09:42.973 --> 09:44.540
So...

09:44.584 --> 09:47.848
Feel like I'm on the wrong side.

09:47.891 --> 09:49.806
You're on
the right side.

09:49.850 --> 09:50.677
You're not.

09:50.720 --> 09:52.635
Gonna break me out?

09:52.679 --> 09:54.811
Too tiring.
All that running.

09:54.855 --> 09:57.814
Yeah, well, maybe you should
have lost the cowboy boots.

09:57.858 --> 10:00.512
You scared?

10:03.341 --> 10:05.648
I'm getting you
out of here, man.No, Linc...

10:05.692 --> 10:07.694
Listen, the Consulate's
arranged to transfer you

10:07.737 --> 10:09.086
to a safer facility
until the trial...

10:09.130 --> 10:10.784
which-which is about a month.

10:10.827 --> 10:13.743
They say you got
a good shot of walking
out of here a free man.

10:13.787 --> 10:15.136
When's the transfer?

10:15.179 --> 10:16.354
Tomorrow.

10:16.398 --> 10:18.966
Just... just hold on,
man, one more day.

10:19.009 --> 10:22.273
You know, I keep waiting for you
to mention a certain someone.

10:24.711 --> 10:26.800
I don't know where she is, man.

10:26.843 --> 10:28.584
Well, you got to find her.

10:28.628 --> 10:29.541
I will.

10:29.585 --> 10:33.981
She's important
to me, Linc.

10:34.024 --> 10:37.462
If anything happens to Sara...

10:39.943 --> 10:42.772
It's going to be fine, man.

10:42.816 --> 10:45.732
I promise.

10:45.775 --> 10:49.692
I'll see you tomorrow.

10:49.736 --> 10:52.129
All right?

11:06.013 --> 11:09.277
[music blasting over stereo]

11:13.760 --> 11:14.935
American, right?

11:14.978 --> 11:16.719
I love America.

11:16.763 --> 11:20.114
NBA. Tracy McGrady
shooting the ball in
the hoop from downtown.

11:20.157 --> 11:21.768
Whatever you're selling,
I'm not buying.

11:21.811 --> 11:23.683
Selling?

11:23.726 --> 11:25.728
I just want to talk
basketball.

11:25.772 --> 11:26.773
Who's your team?

11:29.993 --> 11:31.299
Let's go, blanco.

11:31.342 --> 11:32.387
Orientation.

11:32.430 --> 11:33.257
I'm not interested.

11:33.301 --> 11:35.346
It's not for you to decide.

11:50.013 --> 11:52.320
[knock at door]

11:53.887 --> 11:55.497
Bring them in.

12:12.906 --> 12:15.865
Well, I hope they haven't been
treating you too poorly.

12:15.909 --> 12:17.911
I should hear
of it if you have.

12:17.954 --> 12:21.044
I think as you can tell,
Sona is unlike any other
place in the world.

12:21.088 --> 12:24.265
Huh? Since the riots of last
year, they left us here to rot.

12:24.308 --> 12:25.962
They figured we would
just destroy ourselves,

12:26.006 --> 12:27.834
but instead, we've thrived.

12:27.877 --> 12:30.271
With the canal,
Panama is now

12:30.314 --> 12:32.055
a breeding ground for
international crime.

12:32.099 --> 12:35.015
27 different nationalities
we have here.

12:35.058 --> 12:37.887
But not one gang.

12:37.931 --> 12:40.542
Not one racially-motivated
incident.

12:40.585 --> 12:41.848
Huh?

12:41.891 --> 12:44.328
It's just... me.

12:44.372 --> 12:47.679
Egalitarianism,

12:47.723 --> 12:49.856
I believe, is the word.

12:49.899 --> 12:52.336
Huh? Did I get that right?

12:52.380 --> 12:53.990
Right as rain.

12:55.426 --> 12:57.646
That's what practice
does for you.

12:57.689 --> 13:02.085
Now, is there anything, uh...
you want to tell me?

13:02.129 --> 13:03.434
Any history that you

13:03.478 --> 13:06.786
bring to this place
I should know about?

13:14.576 --> 13:17.840
I don't think you're
quite telling me the truth,

13:17.884 --> 13:19.581
Mr. Scofield.

13:19.624 --> 13:21.278
We get the news, man.

13:21.322 --> 13:24.412
You were quite the superstar

13:24.455 --> 13:25.979
on CNN.

13:26.022 --> 13:27.545
Man breaks brother out...

13:27.589 --> 13:29.330
and flees to Panama.

13:29.373 --> 13:31.071
[laughing]

13:31.114 --> 13:32.463
But you're not

13:32.507 --> 13:33.421
a superstar here!

13:33.464 --> 13:34.335
You realize that,
don't you?

13:34.378 --> 13:35.945
I'm not going to make waves.

13:37.947 --> 13:39.601
It wouldn't be
within your power.

13:46.042 --> 13:48.958
And I heard about
the two of you.

13:49.002 --> 13:50.481
In the hall today.

13:50.525 --> 13:52.744
Now, if you would like to
sort your problems out,

13:52.788 --> 13:54.442
it's very simple here.

13:56.966 --> 14:00.883
A man has a beef with another,
he makes his problem known.

14:00.927 --> 14:02.058
Huh?

14:02.102 --> 14:04.017
And then we deal
with it directly

14:04.060 --> 14:07.542
as men... over there.

14:07.585 --> 14:10.632
Won't be necessary.

14:20.424 --> 14:23.732
You always
shake like that?

14:23.775 --> 14:24.951
Huh?

14:24.994 --> 14:27.083
Or just when you're
scared of someone?

14:33.089 --> 14:35.962
[chuckles]

14:52.500 --> 14:56.156
[blows landing]

14:56.199 --> 14:57.200
I think he gets the message.

14:57.244 --> 14:59.507
[mutters angrily]

15:02.162 --> 15:03.946
We could go... you and me...

15:03.990 --> 15:05.513
right here.

15:07.036 --> 15:09.038
[chuckles lightly]

15:09.082 --> 15:12.085
You're a brave man, huh?

15:12.128 --> 15:15.392
Brave man.

15:17.003 --> 15:18.874
You're lucky I've
been meditating.

15:18.918 --> 15:21.746
Before, I couldn't
take my finger off the
trigger, but now...

15:21.790 --> 15:24.097
now I have mind control.

15:24.140 --> 15:27.448
Complete control.

15:27.491 --> 15:28.971
Mind...

15:29.015 --> 15:30.799
body...

15:30.842 --> 15:32.018
and soul.

15:35.021 --> 15:35.935
Get out!

15:37.110 --> 15:39.590
Get out!

15:47.947 --> 15:49.296
Complete waste
of our time.

15:49.339 --> 15:52.952
Who would have thought...
a famous person in Sona?

15:52.995 --> 15:55.519
Weak people
rally around fame.

15:55.563 --> 15:56.868
They worship it.
They're blinded by it.

15:56.912 --> 15:59.219
And as you can tell,
there are many people

15:59.262 --> 16:00.829
of weak character
behind these walls.

16:00.872 --> 16:02.657
Yes, they will follow
a man like this,

16:02.700 --> 16:05.355
and they will put him
on a pedestal.

16:05.399 --> 16:11.100
He has that charisma,
right, mami?

16:11.144 --> 16:12.667
He's no you.

16:12.710 --> 16:15.322
Ah, you don't have
to pander me, mami.

16:15.365 --> 16:17.193
Soy un hombre maduro.
Huh?

16:17.237 --> 16:18.629
He's good looking, right?

16:20.501 --> 16:21.981
Sí.

16:23.765 --> 16:26.202
He's the best looking
man in the prison, right?

16:26.246 --> 16:28.117
Not compared to you.

16:28.161 --> 16:29.205
[gasps]

16:29.249 --> 16:30.206
I told you, mami...

17:01.237 --> 17:03.718
♪

17:16.296 --> 17:18.037
[song blasts over radio]

17:27.872 --> 17:29.744
MICHAEL:
Sara...

17:42.626 --> 17:44.106
Sara Tancredi--
she's an American.

17:44.150 --> 17:45.412
She's missing.

17:45.455 --> 17:46.978
We don't have a report
of anything like that.

17:47.022 --> 17:49.633
But if you do, you call me;
the number's on the back.

17:49.677 --> 17:51.548
Okay, señor.

17:51.592 --> 17:53.942
Anything, you call me,
all right?

17:53.985 --> 17:54.725
Will do.

17:54.769 --> 17:57.163
Thank you.

18:05.823 --> 18:07.173
Where'd you get shoes?

18:11.133 --> 18:13.179
[flies buzzing]

18:15.094 --> 18:16.617
Hey, hey!

18:16.660 --> 18:18.967
It's time to start earning
your rent around here.

18:19.010 --> 18:19.881
There's no rent here.

18:19.924 --> 18:21.361
It's prison.Keep talking.

18:21.404 --> 18:23.145
It's going up.

18:23.189 --> 18:24.364
Here.

18:24.407 --> 18:26.148
Work time's started
right now.

18:26.192 --> 18:29.543
Where?

18:31.719 --> 18:33.155
Uh-uh. Hell, no.

18:33.199 --> 18:34.330
Absolutely not.

18:34.374 --> 18:35.549
[blow lands]

18:36.506 --> 18:38.204
One more word from you,

18:38.247 --> 18:40.075
and I will drown you
in here, you understand?

18:42.686 --> 18:44.166
Now, work.

18:44.210 --> 18:47.082
Burn it down in
the sewers when
you're done.

18:49.258 --> 18:51.956
♪

19:02.445 --> 19:06.275
♪

19:36.740 --> 19:40.135
♪

19:54.628 --> 19:57.457
MAN [over intercom]:
Scofield, visita.

19:57.500 --> 19:59.415
Scofield, visita.

20:01.025 --> 20:03.027
[door bangs shut]

20:06.292 --> 20:07.771
Ah, Mr. Scofield.

20:07.815 --> 20:09.599
Elliot Pike.What do you want?

20:09.643 --> 20:12.167
Well, to be frank,
to represent you.

20:12.211 --> 20:13.690
You're a lawyer?
Of sorts.

20:13.734 --> 20:16.040
The court already
appointed me a lawyer.

20:17.868 --> 20:22.482
Then perhaps I can be of
assistance in a different way.

20:22.525 --> 20:24.135
Somehow I doubt that.

20:24.179 --> 20:26.834
I got a lot of big guns
behind me, Mr. Scofield,

20:26.877 --> 20:29.140
people you might like
to have in your corner

20:29.184 --> 20:33.014
should you ever decide,
say... to break out of here.

20:36.757 --> 20:37.932
Who are you?

20:37.975 --> 20:40.761
We can assist you
in every possible way

20:40.804 --> 20:42.850
once you get past that wall.

20:46.636 --> 20:48.899
There's a reason
a guy like you,

20:48.943 --> 20:51.337
with your skill set,
was put in here, you know.

20:53.469 --> 20:55.906
This conversation's over.

20:55.950 --> 20:57.995
You ought to hear
what I have to say, Scofield.

20:58.039 --> 21:00.041
We're trying to do
this the easy way.

21:10.747 --> 21:13.402
[drumming continues in distance]

21:31.942 --> 21:34.293
What the hell are you doing
taking my stash, huh?

21:34.336 --> 21:36.295
Cough it up,
you little bitch.

21:36.338 --> 21:37.861
I didn't do it.Where is it?!

21:37.905 --> 21:40.211
Where is it, huh?!It wasn't me.

21:43.563 --> 21:46.130
Hey!

21:46.174 --> 21:49.264
You know the rules about
extra-curricular fights!

21:49.308 --> 21:50.874
It doesn't happen here.

21:50.918 --> 21:53.094
He took something
that belongs to me.

21:53.137 --> 21:54.008
He's out of his mind.

21:54.051 --> 21:55.488
Well, it seems
pretty easy

21:55.531 --> 21:57.925
to get to the bottom
of this-- check him.

22:05.019 --> 22:07.108
Check his area.

22:17.292 --> 22:19.163
That's bull.

22:22.297 --> 22:23.385
You're both

22:23.429 --> 22:25.822
scumbags.

22:30.131 --> 22:31.393
You and me, man.

22:31.437 --> 22:32.481
We're not done here.

22:37.704 --> 22:40.446
You haven't seen her?
No one like this has checked in?

22:40.489 --> 22:42.186
No, señor.

22:42.230 --> 22:43.274
You're absolutely sure?

22:43.318 --> 22:45.407
[cell phone rings]Sí.

22:45.451 --> 22:47.453
Thanks.

22:48.758 --> 22:49.759
Yeah.

22:49.803 --> 22:52.632
Mr. Burrows.
Captain Itzuris

22:52.675 --> 22:54.024
at the constable's office.

22:54.068 --> 22:57.463
We found an American woman
matching the description

22:57.506 --> 23:00.161
of your friend, Ms. Tancredi.

23:00.204 --> 23:02.337
Where?

23:02.381 --> 23:04.295
At the morgue.

23:12.869 --> 23:14.436
Uh, por favor, señor.

23:14.480 --> 23:16.482
[speaks Spanish]

23:16.525 --> 23:17.700
What's he saying?

23:17.744 --> 23:19.441
That we can't eat.

23:19.485 --> 23:21.008
What are we
supposed to eat?

23:36.197 --> 23:38.982
They expect us to forage,
like dogs.

23:39.026 --> 23:41.550
I'll die.
I will literally die.

23:41.594 --> 23:45.032
[sobbing]

23:47.687 --> 23:49.340
Hang in there, man.

24:09.578 --> 24:13.408
♪

24:21.764 --> 24:24.506
Playing by yourself.
Same old Pretty.

24:24.550 --> 24:26.856
Just not good
at making friends, are you?

24:26.900 --> 24:29.119
We got nothing to say
to each other.

24:29.163 --> 24:30.512
On another note,

24:30.556 --> 24:32.514
on a big picture note,
them big government types

24:32.558 --> 24:34.560
that shook me down so hard,
why is it they wanted you here?

24:34.603 --> 24:35.909
Was it Sona they was
interested in?

24:35.952 --> 24:37.388
That's what I'm thinking.

24:37.432 --> 24:39.956
Want me to get you down here,
up in this very county.

24:40.000 --> 24:41.610
What do you think
it is, huh?

24:41.654 --> 24:42.916
You think it's Sona?

24:42.959 --> 24:44.874
Who'd be interested
in a dump like this?

24:44.918 --> 24:48.443
MEN:
Runner! Runner!

24:54.275 --> 24:56.059
[clamoring shouts]

25:12.511 --> 25:13.990
Stop!

25:14.034 --> 25:16.166
No! No!

25:17.646 --> 25:19.343
[automatic gunfire]

25:27.613 --> 25:29.353
[loud murmuring]

25:37.623 --> 25:40.495
[breathing heavily]

26:04.650 --> 26:06.956
LINCOLN:
Thanks for getting back to me.ITZURIS: No problem.

26:07.000 --> 26:09.132
The body was fished
out of the pond

26:09.176 --> 26:11.352
first thing this morning.Where?

26:11.395 --> 26:14.007
Calle Sesenta-Seis.

26:14.050 --> 26:16.009
Just west of Avenida Colon.

26:18.968 --> 26:20.796
Sir?

26:20.840 --> 26:23.277
That's the last
place I saw her.

26:39.772 --> 26:41.600
It's not her.

26:43.210 --> 26:45.212
It's not her.

26:58.921 --> 27:01.315
Someone's thrown the glove
down on you.

27:01.358 --> 27:02.795
The gauntlet, right?

27:02.838 --> 27:04.753
Yeah, except we both know
I didn't take those drugs.

27:04.797 --> 27:06.712
I'm not the judge.

27:06.755 --> 27:08.757
I don't deal in the claims
people make.

27:08.801 --> 27:09.932
I just make sure the
rules are followed.

27:09.976 --> 27:11.542
And the rules say

27:11.586 --> 27:14.415
all grievances are dealt with
two men in a ring-- a fight.

27:14.458 --> 27:17.636
I'll be leaving tomorrow,
so that won't be necessary.

27:17.679 --> 27:19.812
It may not be necessary to you,

27:19.855 --> 27:20.987
but it is to me.

27:21.030 --> 27:23.946
I have a duty
to maintain order here--

27:23.990 --> 27:26.209
an ironclad legal system
that assures that

27:26.253 --> 27:28.559
no one goes independent
with their grievances,

27:28.603 --> 27:30.823
as is so often the case
in other prisons.

27:30.866 --> 27:31.867
Here,

27:31.911 --> 27:32.825
there is a system,

27:32.868 --> 27:34.870
and that system means order.

27:34.914 --> 27:36.829
So whether you
agree with it or not

27:36.872 --> 27:38.874
does not matter to me.

27:38.918 --> 27:40.659
There's a larger
agenda than yours.

27:45.054 --> 27:46.882
What happens if I refuse?

27:47.883 --> 27:50.973
We'll come for you.

27:51.017 --> 27:53.933
And I can guarantee you
that is an outcome

27:53.976 --> 27:55.935
that you will not like.

27:55.978 --> 27:57.806
Tell me something...

27:57.850 --> 27:59.286
do you always set up
your fights?

27:59.329 --> 28:02.419
[chuckles]
I had nothing
to do with it.

28:02.463 --> 28:04.770
And yet the only one
in this whole prison

28:04.813 --> 28:06.815
who has a problem with me
is you.

28:06.859 --> 28:09.775
I'll be glad to see
you go down...

28:09.818 --> 28:12.299
superstar.

28:15.911 --> 28:20.263
[water dripping]

28:22.831 --> 28:24.093
Go on, keep going.

28:24.137 --> 28:26.792
You burn it
around the corner.

28:26.835 --> 28:28.358
Move it!

28:31.884 --> 28:33.537
[soft whistle]

28:39.718 --> 28:41.807
[airy whistle]

28:50.293 --> 28:52.382
MAN:
Hey.

28:58.867 --> 29:00.913
[hoarse]:
Hey.

29:05.656 --> 29:07.615
[Australian accent]:
Think you can do me a favor?

29:07.658 --> 29:09.791
Bite me.

29:09.835 --> 29:11.750
I can feed you.

29:12.925 --> 29:15.710
A few weeks ago, I
was in your shoes.

29:15.754 --> 29:18.017
Didn't get any food for days.

29:18.060 --> 29:19.148
They'd have let me die,

29:19.192 --> 29:20.846
just like they're
gonna let you die.

29:20.889 --> 29:22.412
Get back to the "feed me" part.

29:26.895 --> 29:28.897
Chicken.

29:28.941 --> 29:30.638
Man, where'd you get

29:30.681 --> 29:31.900
chicken?

29:31.944 --> 29:33.728
That's not chicken.

29:38.777 --> 29:40.953
Want some more?
Yeah.

29:40.996 --> 29:43.999
Then you're gonna have
to run an errand for me.

29:44.043 --> 29:46.480
What kind of errand?

29:51.093 --> 29:54.009
[cell phone ringing]

29:54.053 --> 29:55.924
LINCOLN:
Yeah.

29:55.968 --> 29:58.448
Dad? It's me.LJ.

29:58.492 --> 29:59.754
Where are you?

29:59.798 --> 30:01.147
I'm in Panama.

30:01.190 --> 30:03.236
What?

30:03.279 --> 30:04.672
How...

30:04.715 --> 30:05.934
How'd you get this number?

30:05.978 --> 30:07.327
Well, I ran into Sara.

30:07.370 --> 30:09.372
She got your number
from the consulate.

30:09.416 --> 30:10.983
Dad, I'm cutting out.LJ...?

30:11.026 --> 30:12.854
[static bursting]I can't hear you.

30:12.898 --> 30:14.421
Dad, do this.

30:14.464 --> 30:17.032
Meet us at the restaurant
in the Garfield Price building

30:17.076 --> 30:18.033
at the top.

30:18.077 --> 30:18.991
Garfield what?

30:19.034 --> 30:22.298
8:30... [call drops]

30:28.087 --> 30:31.612
[inmates shouting,
clapping rhythmically]

30:34.354 --> 30:37.270
Time to fight,
blanco.

30:38.053 --> 30:41.056
[clapping rhythmically]

30:43.450 --> 30:47.280
Best to make your
peace with God, eh?

30:53.982 --> 30:55.549
What? Even at 10-1?

30:55.592 --> 30:57.943
There's a reason
he chose World.

30:57.986 --> 31:00.510
Six consecutive
life terms, okay?

31:00.554 --> 31:03.862
[speaking Spanish]

31:13.001 --> 31:14.089
[laughing]:
I'm just kidding, man.

31:14.133 --> 31:17.876
Tranquilo!

31:23.055 --> 31:25.492
Surely, it's beneath
a man of your status

31:25.535 --> 31:27.102
to be walking
around like that,

31:27.146 --> 31:28.887
all sticky-like.

31:28.930 --> 31:30.018
Leave him.

31:30.062 --> 31:31.933
What do you propose?

31:31.977 --> 31:34.762
Ablution.

31:34.805 --> 31:36.372
[laughs]

31:36.416 --> 31:40.159
A humble sign
of friendship
from a stranger

31:40.202 --> 31:42.552
who's come into your house.

31:50.082 --> 31:51.822
Sorry about that.

31:51.866 --> 31:55.043
Just half a man down here.

31:57.045 --> 31:59.047
What's your name,
norteño?

31:59.091 --> 32:04.487
You can just
call me "friend."

32:13.627 --> 32:15.716
Go for the kneecap.

32:17.065 --> 32:19.459
You, uh... you hit it

32:19.502 --> 32:20.721
straight on,
it'll buckle,

32:20.764 --> 32:24.029
and you'll take the guy
out of commission.

32:24.072 --> 32:26.422
Fighting dirty?
That's your secret?

32:26.466 --> 32:29.121
I didn't think there was
any such thing as clean

32:29.164 --> 32:31.297
in a place like this.

32:31.340 --> 32:34.126
You know, I'm surprised, Alex.

32:34.169 --> 32:36.084
It almost sounds like you care.

32:36.128 --> 32:38.957
You're my
get-out-of-jail-free card.

32:40.697 --> 32:42.612
Just survive.

32:45.093 --> 32:46.790
Kneecap, really hard.

32:50.011 --> 32:52.448
[sighs sharply]

32:54.146 --> 32:56.975
[inmates yelling]

33:12.773 --> 33:16.211
[yelling continues]

33:27.048 --> 33:28.484
Good luck, man.

33:31.792 --> 33:35.970
[yelling continues]

33:57.209 --> 33:59.211
God bless, man.

33:59.254 --> 34:02.040
[yelling continues]

34:09.221 --> 34:13.268
We have a disagreement
between two dogs--

34:13.312 --> 34:15.749
a drug addict and a thief.

34:15.792 --> 34:18.186
And I condone neither.

34:18.230 --> 34:19.927
And I wash my hands
of both of them.

34:19.970 --> 34:23.452
But they have an issue,
and we have rules.

34:23.496 --> 34:26.673
And without rules, we're
nothing but savages.

34:26.716 --> 34:28.936
Therefore, with proper
respect for the rules,

34:28.979 --> 34:32.287
this fight is engaged
with only one rule--

34:32.331 --> 34:34.289
no weapons.

34:34.333 --> 34:36.161
Only man versus man,

34:36.204 --> 34:39.164
without augmentation
or handicap.

34:40.165 --> 34:41.383
I'm done talking.

34:41.427 --> 34:45.561
[intense shouting]

34:52.916 --> 34:54.570
I'm not going to fight!

35:12.197 --> 35:15.069
[shouting]

35:28.038 --> 35:32.086
I don't think you
understand the rules, friend.

35:32.130 --> 35:33.957
Only one man comes out alive.

35:35.350 --> 35:37.570
[inmates yelling]

35:46.927 --> 35:48.711
[inmates yelling]

36:00.288 --> 36:02.725
[yelling continues]

36:08.688 --> 36:09.906
It's over!

36:09.950 --> 36:12.344
INMATE: Finish it!MICHAEL:
Let me through.

36:12.387 --> 36:13.823
Let me go.

36:21.483 --> 36:23.224
[bone snapping]

36:23.268 --> 36:24.399
[panting]

36:28.664 --> 36:30.362
MAHONE:
No weapons!

36:30.405 --> 36:32.799
Rules are rules.
Remember?

36:35.149 --> 36:37.151
And if we don't have them...

36:37.195 --> 36:39.284
we're savages.

37:03.960 --> 37:05.266
Oh, excuse me.

37:05.310 --> 37:06.876
You have no jacket.

37:06.920 --> 37:08.530
Come on, man. I'm just meeting
someone. Give me a break.

37:08.574 --> 37:10.532
Well, this is a nice place.

37:10.576 --> 37:11.751
It requires jackets.

37:11.794 --> 37:14.014
Well, I don't
have a jacket.

37:14.057 --> 37:15.233
It requires jackets.

37:17.235 --> 37:18.061
Fine.

37:26.809 --> 37:28.420
Excuse me.

37:28.463 --> 37:30.030
You speak English?

37:30.073 --> 37:32.685
How about American?

37:47.352 --> 37:49.832
Can I grab a water, please?

37:49.876 --> 37:51.007
Please tell me
you didn't come

37:51.051 --> 37:53.706
all the way to Panama
for the water.

37:55.360 --> 37:58.058
Family.

37:59.494 --> 38:02.541
That's a nice jacket, Sergio.

38:02.584 --> 38:06.284
It's a long story.

38:06.327 --> 38:07.850
Thank you.

38:07.894 --> 38:10.418
You're waiting for someone, huh?

38:10.462 --> 38:11.376
Uh-huh.

38:11.419 --> 38:12.507
I should
have known.

38:12.551 --> 38:14.770
Good-looking ones
are always taken.

38:18.557 --> 38:20.646
What happened
to your face?

38:20.689 --> 38:22.038
A cat.

38:22.082 --> 38:24.040
Cat. It's a big cat.

38:24.084 --> 38:26.521
You push anything
too far into a corner,

38:26.565 --> 38:28.306
and the claws will come out.

38:30.612 --> 38:32.571
Your timing's all wrong, lady.

38:32.614 --> 38:33.876
Oh, come on. Hang out.

38:33.920 --> 38:38.403
I'd like to...
but it ain't the right time.

38:40.492 --> 38:43.277
Yes, it is, Lincoln.

38:47.194 --> 38:48.804
We have a lot to discuss.

38:48.848 --> 38:50.806
Specifically, your brother.

38:55.420 --> 38:57.422
I highly suggest

38:57.465 --> 39:00.033
you talk to him.

39:14.700 --> 39:18.268
[woman shouting in Spanish]

39:32.587 --> 39:34.807
WOMAN:
Hey!

39:49.517 --> 39:51.171
[indistinct voices]

40:02.530 --> 40:05.228
♪

40:21.114 --> 40:23.899
[gunshots]

40:32.604 --> 40:35.389
[flies buzzing]

41:04.679 --> 41:07.465
♪

41:24.482 --> 41:26.571
Hey.

41:27.920 --> 41:29.574
How are we coming
with the transfer?

41:31.706 --> 41:33.055
There are some people

41:33.099 --> 41:35.449
that want you
to break someone out of there.

41:35.493 --> 41:36.537
Yeah, I know.

41:36.581 --> 41:37.799
Some guy already approached me.

41:37.843 --> 41:39.148
I said, "No, thank you."

41:39.192 --> 41:40.976
You got to stay.

41:41.020 --> 41:43.849
What are you talking about?

41:43.892 --> 41:45.590
LINCOLN:
His name's James Whistler.

41:45.633 --> 41:47.983
No, no, no, no, Linc,
I can't do that again.

41:48.027 --> 41:50.508
Michael.

41:53.772 --> 41:55.774
MAN:
Talk.

41:55.817 --> 41:56.992
Dad.

41:57.819 --> 42:00.692
Dad, I'm so sorry.

42:00.735 --> 42:02.389
They got me and Sara.

42:02.432 --> 42:05.784
Please, do what they want.

42:05.827 --> 42:06.741
Dad, please.

42:06.785 --> 42:09.396
You got a week

42:09.439 --> 42:10.789
to find this Whistler guy.

42:10.832 --> 42:12.660
Get him out of there.

42:12.704 --> 42:14.227
Otherwise, they, uh...

42:14.270 --> 42:15.663
Sara and LJ...

42:15.707 --> 42:17.622
they both die.
